obo:BFO_0000050  a  owl:ObjectProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_262  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Flotillin-2 regulates in cooperation with Rab11a membrane trafficking processes in spines and participates in LTP-related AMPA receptor (GluA1) surface exposure in mouse hippocampal neurons.\n\n13/4/2017 Pim\nFig.1 A-G\n- shRNA KD of Reggie1 or reggie2 results in less spines --> regulation of dendritic spine organization\n- Reggie1 KO mouse no effect on spine number, but less spine synapses --> regulation of synapse organization\n\nFig.1 G-J\n- Reggie1 and Reggie2 localize to synaptic component transport vesicles in dendrites.\n\nFig.2 A,B\n- RFP-Reggie1 is co-transported with PSD-95 in dendrites\n\nFig.2 C-Fig\n- Reggie1 KD causes reduction in number of spine synapses (measured as juxtaposed presynaptic FM4-64FX and postsynaptic PSD-95-EGFP staining).\n\nFig.3\n- Reggie1 KO cells show impaired transport of PSD-95, and reduced number of synapses (measured as juxtaposed synaptophysin/PSD-95 staining). Experimental description: Hippocampal neurons from 1 to 2 d old wt C57BL/6J and reggie-1 k.o. (Flot2-/-) mice. (p 32)\nReggie-1 knock-out (k.o.; Flot2 -/-) C57BL/6J mice were generously provided by Tak W. Mak (The Campbell Family Institute for Breast Cancer Research, University Toronto, Canada; Berger et al., 2013). K.o. and wild type (wt) C57BL/6J mice were raised in the animal facility, University of Konstanz. Male and female mice, 1-2 d and 2 months old, were used.\n\n20/3/2017 Pim\n- The species of overexpression constructs used in this paper are not relevant for species determination since they merely serve as specificity controls for KD/KO conditions.\n- Species of RFP-reggie1 (Fig.2A,B) was traced back to **rat** origin based on PMID:17854803:\n\"Deletion mutants of reggie-1 were obtained by PCR using rat full-length reggie-1 cloned in pEGFP-N1 (Clontech, Heidelberg, Germany) (R1FL-EGFP)\". This species does not prevent annotation to mouse species.\n- Species of PSD-95-EGFP was traced to rat by email communication with David Brendt:\n\n\" 13 April 2017 19:34\nThis is rat.\n\nDavid\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9681-3318" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0269-0311" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9880-1214" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9377-7414" ;
        dc:date           "2017-04-13" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_262" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

